The Kenya Pipeline Company has reassured the country it has sufficient fuel reserves in its depot amid the ongoing crisis. Managing director Irungu Macharia said on Wednesday "The only thing I can assure you your excellency is that Kenya Pipeline is so full of prodcut I don't know where to take it," Macharia said. “We are so wet, the country has all the fuel it requires,” he added. He spoke at a meeting where ODM leader Raila Odinga met with fuel stakeholders to discuss the crisis.